description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you committed to a positive future in Primary Care?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Due to exciting expansion and the innovative re-design of our non-clinical workforce, Laurie Pike Health Centre is looking to recruit Patient Services Assistants within the Modality Birmingham Division.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who are Modality Partnership?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A growing super partnership providing primary care services to patients across multiple GP Surgeries throughout the UK.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Our focus is on delivering innovative, high quality patient-centred care whilst providing a supportive working environment for our multi-disciplinary teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commitment to developing and sustaining a learning environment for exceptional health professionals of the future&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with local colleagues to deliver integrated care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proud of our professional friendly team who look after our patients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provider of established and high quality services on site (outpatients, diagnostic, mental health, surgical)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we offer?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A caring and supporting working environment for all our staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentorship&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team meetings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Training and Development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full induction programme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Protected learning time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunities to follow a career escalator&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In-house practice meetings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Internal development appraisals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fairness, equality and honesty&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Practice social events&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What we expect from our Patient Services Assistants;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Previous GP experience is essential for all applicants.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To interact with patients to provide and process information in response to inquiries, concerns and requests about NHS service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dedicated, flexible individuals with high aspirations for themselves and for integrated primary care teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Key skills in customer service, communication, listening and problem solving&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of relevant computer applications, Microsoft Word and TPP SystmOne&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Applicants will be required to complete a Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) application&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
